sh Charts|Suomen virallinen lista]])<ref>{{cite book|first= Jake |last= Nyman |title= Suomi soi 4: Suuri suomalainen listakirja |edition= 1st |year= 2005 |publisher= Tammi |location= Helsinki |isbn= 951-31-2503-3 |language= fi}}</ref> \n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{single chart|France|1|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|2|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|songid=2601|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n|Iceland ([[\u00cdslenski listinn|\u00cdslenski Listinn Topp 40]])<ref>{{cite magazine|title= \u00cdslenski Listinn: Topp 40: Vikan 28. Mai \u2013 3. Juni |magazine= Dagbla\u00f0i\u00f0 V\u00edsir |date= 27 May 1993 |page= 29 |accessdate= 4 February 2018 |url= http://timarit.is/files/11729281.pdf#navpanes=1&view=FitH}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland2|1|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n|Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|title= SINGOLI \u2013 I NUMERI UNO (1959-2006) (parte 4: 1990-1996) |publisher= It-charts.150m.com |url= http://it-charts.150m.com/numeriuno-1990.htm |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |language= it |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110707055417/http://it-charts.150m.com/numeriuno-1990.htm |archivedate= 7 July 2011}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch40|1|artist=Haddaway - What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch100|1|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|New Zealand|48|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Norway|1|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n|Portugal ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica Portuguesa|AFP]])<ref>{{cite magazine|title= Top 10 Sales in Europe |magazine= [[Music & Media]] |date= 11 September 1993 |volume= 10 |issue= 37 |page= 14 |url= http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1993/MM-1993-09-11.pdf |accessdate= 26 February 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|AFYVE]])<ref name=\"SP\">{{cite book|first= Fernando |last= Salaverri |title= S\u00f3lo \u00e9xitos: a\u00f1o a a\u00f1o, 1959\u20132002 |edition= 1st |date= September 2005 |publisher= Fundaci\u00f3n Autor-SGAE |location= Spain |isbn= 84-8048-639-2 |language= es}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{single chart|Sweden|2|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Switzerland|1|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|2|date=1993-07-03|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|title= Haddaway \u2013 Awards |website= [[AllMusic]] |url= http://www.allmusic.com/artist/haddaway-mn0000548196/awards |accessdate= 23 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|11\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Club Play]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|9\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Dance/Electronic Singles Sales|Hot Dance Music/Maxi-Singles Sales]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|6\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Rhythmic (chart)|Rhythmic Top 40]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|15\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Top 40|Top 40 Mainstream]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n|US [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'']]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/90s_files/19931030.html |title= CASH BOX Top 100 Singles \u2013 Week ending OCTOBER 30, 1993 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121010195217/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/90s_files/19931030.html |archivedate= 10 October 2012}}. [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'' magazine]].</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|9\n|-\n|Zimbabwe ([[List of record charts|ZIMA]])<ref>{{cite book|first= Chris |last= Kimberley |year= 2000 |title= Zimbabwe : Zimbabwe Singles Chart Book |location= Harare}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2020)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Poland|51|chartid=3322|year=2020|accessdate=24 February 2020}}\n|-\n|Slovenia ([[SloTop50]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Tedenska lestvica > 14 Teden: 30.03.2020 \u2013 05.04.2020 |publisher= [[SloTop50]] |accessdate= 6 April 2020 |url= https://www.slotop50.si/Glasbene-lestvice/Tedenske-lestvice/?year=2020&week=14}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|46\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====\"What Is Love\" \u2013 Remix====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1993)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Swiss|15|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love - Remix|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|AFYVE]])<ref name=\"SP\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|4\n|}\n\n====\"What Is Love\" \u2013 Reloaded====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2003)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Austrian|49|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love - Reloaded|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Denmark|20|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love - Reloaded|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n|Germany ([[GfK Entertainment|Media Control Charts]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Single \u2013 Haddaway, What Is Love \u2013 Reloaded |publisher= Officialcharts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]] |url= http://www.officialcharts.de/song.asp?artist=Haddaway&title=What%20Is%20Love%20-%20Reloaded&country=de |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141025150241/http://www.officialcharts.de/song.asp?artist=Haddaway&title=What%2BIs%2BLove%2B-%2BReloaded&country=de |archivedate= 25 October 2014 |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|51\n|-\n|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|title= dutchcharts.nl \u2013 Haddaway \u2013 What Is Love \u2013 Reloaded |publisher= [[Single Top 100]]. Hung Medien |url= http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Haddaway&titel=What+Is+Love+-+Reloaded&cat=s |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|100\n|-\n|Switzerland ([[Swiss Hitparade|Schweizer Hitparade]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Haddaway \u2013 What Is Love \u2013 Reloaded \u2013 hitparade.ch |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= http://hitparade.ch/showitem.asp?interpret=Haddaway&titel=What+Is+Love+-+Reloaded&cat=s |publisher= Hitparade.ch. Hung Medien |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|92\n|}\n\n====Other reissues====\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2008)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Digital Songs|Hot Digital Songs]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|68\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2012)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Danish|31|artist=Haddaway|song=What Is Love|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1993)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref name=\"ryan\">{{cite book|first= Gavin |last= Ryan |title= Australia's Music Charts 1988\u20132010 |year= 2011 |publisher= Moonlight Publishing |location= Mt. Martha, VIC, Australia}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|78\n|-\n|Austria ([[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jahreshitparade 1993 |publisher= Austriancharts.at. Hung Medien |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= http://www.austriancharts.at/1993_single.asp |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|Belgium ([[Ultratop|Ultratop 50]] Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|title= Jaaroverzichten 1993 |publisher= [[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1993 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|Canada Dance/Urban (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite magazine|title= The RPM Top 50 Dance Tracks of 1993 |magazine= [[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |publisher= [[Library and Archives Canada]] |volume= 58 |issue= 23 |date= 18 December 1993 |accessdate= 1 October 2018 |url= http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.2328&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.2328.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.2328}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|Europe ([[Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|title= 1993 Year-End Sales Charts |magazine= [[Music & Media]] |volume= 10 |issue= 51/52 |page= 15 |date= 18 December 1993 |accessdate= 18 November 2019 |url= https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1993/MM-1993-12-18.pdf}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|Germany ([[GfK Entertainment|Media Control Charts]])<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.officialcharts.de/year.asp?cat=s&country=de&year=1993&x=39&y=5 |title= Jahrescharts \u2013 1993 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140714201900/http://www.officialcharts.de/year.asp?cat=s&country=de&year=1993&x=39&y=5 |archivedate= 14 July 2014|language=de}}. Officialcharts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]].</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|title= I singoli pi\u00f9 venduti del 1993 |publisher= Hit Parade Italia. [[Creative Commons]] |url= http://www.hitparadeitalia.it/hp_yends/hpe1993.htm |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |language= it}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|-\n|Netherlands ([[Dutch Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 1993 |publisher= [[Dutch Top 40]] |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= http://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/1993 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 1993 |publisher= [[Single Top 100]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= http://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1993&cat=s |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n|Switzerland ([[Swiss Hitparade|Schweizer Hitparade]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Schweizer Jahreshitparade 1993 |publisher= Hitparade.ch. Hung Medien |url= http://hitparade.ch/year.asp?key=1993 |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|UK Singles ([[Official Charts Company]])<ref>{{cite book|first= Neil |last= Warwick |first2= Jon |last2= Kutner |first3= Tony |last3= Brown |title= The Complete Book of the British Charts: Singles and Albums |publisher= [[Music Sales Group|Omnibus Press]] |year= 2004 |edition= 3rd |isbn= 978-1-8444-9058-5 }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1993 |title= Top 100 Hits for 1993 |website= The Longbored Surfer |accessdate= 23 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|82\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (1994)\n!Position\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web |title= Top 100 Hits for 1994 |publisher= The Longbored Surfer |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1994.php |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140101130345/http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1994.php |archivedate= 1 January 2014 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|97\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Certifications and sales===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Gold|relyear=1993|certyear=1994|certref=<ref name=\"ryan\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Austria|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Platinum|relyear=1993|certyear=1993}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Denmark|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Gold|relyear=1993|certyear=2017}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Gold|number=3|relyear=1993|certyear=1993}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Sweden|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Gold|relyear=1993|certyear=1993}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Gold|relyear=1993|certyear=1993}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|artist=Haddaway|title=What Is Love|award=Gold|relyear=1993|certyear=1994}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Cover versions and sampling==\n*In 2007, the song was covered by indie band [[Gossip (band)|The Gossip]], with lead singer [[Beth Ditto]] changing the lyrics to \"When Is Lunch?, Baby I'm Hungry, I'm Hungry, For More\".<ref>{{cite news|first= Simon |last= Price |title= Interpol/The Gossip, Reading Festival |newspaper= [[The Independent]] |date= 2 September 2007 |accessdate= 23 January 2014 |url= https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/interpolthe-gossip-reading-festival-463808.html}}</ref>\n*In 2009, singer and songwriter [[Diane Birch]] completely rearranged the song,<ref>{{cite web|title= Diane Birch In Concert |publisher= [[NPR]] |url= https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=105783310 |date= 26 June 2009 |accessdate= 24 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Diane Birch covers Haddaway's \"What Is Love?\" |url= http://loft965.com/2009/07/27/diane-birch-covers-haddaways-what-is-love/ |website= Loft965.com |date= 27 July 2009 |accessdate= 23 January 2014}}</ref> that later was featured on ''Billboard'' magazine's Mashup Monday in 2010.<ref>{{cite magazine|title= Diane Birch De-Clubs \"What Is Love\" |magazine= Billboard |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/mashup-mondays/959122/diane-birch-de-clubs-what-is-love |date= 8 March 2010 |accessdate= 23 January 2014}}</ref>\n*In 2010, [[Sharaya J]] sampled the chorus for her performance on [[Missy Elliott]]'s European tour.<ref>{{cite web|title= Sharaya @ Bamboo Mamaia \u2013 16 iulie 2010 \u2013 HD video 5a |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Bd2b6w3lpA |publisher= [[YouTube]] |date= 16 July 2010 |accessdate= 15 March 2013}}</ref>\n*In 2010, Swedish [[boy band]] [[E.M.D.]] released a piano ballad version of \"What Is Love\" as the second single from their sophomore [[studio album]] ''[[Rewind (E.M.D. album)|Rewind]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title= EMD cover Haddaway's 'What Is Love'! |publisher= Scandipop |date= 28 October 2010 |url= http://www.scandipop.co.uk/emd-cover-haddaways-what-is-love/ |accessdate= 23 January 2014}}</ref>\n*In 2010, American rappers [[Eminem]] and [[Lil Wayne]] sampled the song for the single \"[[No Love]]\" from Eminem's seventh studio album, ''[[Recovery (Eminem album)|Recovery]]''.<ref name=\"Recovery\"/>\n*In 2013, it was covered by the band Foolstop in a rock style.<ref>{{cite web|title= Foolstop \u2013 What Is Love (Haddaway Rock Cover) |publisher= YouTube |date= 30 April 2013 |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LFWw-9fmlmQ |accessdate= 23 January 2014}}</ref>\n*In 2014, Canadian singer [[Kiesza]] did a \"piano-and-synth cover\" of the song.<ref>{{cite web|first= Robbie |last= Daw |title= Kiesza Covers Haddaway's \"What Is Love\": Watch The Video For Her Rendition Of The '90s Classic |url= http://www.idolator.com/7515322/kiesza-cover-haddaway-what-is-love-listen |publisher= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate= 1 May 2014 |date= 23 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Klaas version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Klaas meets Haddaway \u2013 What Is Love 2K9\n| cover      = What-Is-Love-2k9.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Klaas (DJ)|Klaas]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 2009\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      = Mostiko\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Tony Hendrik|Dee Dee Halligan]]|Junior Torello}}\n| producer   = [[Klaas (DJ)|Klaas]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|-YZ9V9-WWgE|\"What is Love 2K9\"}}}}\n}}\nIn 2009, German DJ [[Klaas (DJ)|Klaas]] remixed the song under the title \"Klaas meets Haddaway \u2013 What Is Love 2K9\". This remix charted in several European countries.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2009)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|37|artist=Klaas meets Haddaway|song=What Is Love 2K9|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|41|artist=Klaas meets Haddaway|song=What Is Love 2K9|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|9|artist=Klaas meets Haddaway|song=What Is Love 2K9|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|5|artist=Klaas meets Haddaway|song=What Is Love 2K9|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|60|songid=593843|artist=Klaas meets Haddaway|song=What Is Love 2K9|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|49|artist=Klaas meets Haddaway|song=What Is Love 2K9|accessdate=23 January 2014}}\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n===Lost Frequencies version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = What Is Love 2016\n| cover      = What-Is-Love-2016-Lost-Frequencies.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Lost Frequencies]]\n| album      = [[Less Is More (Lost Frequencies album)|Less Is More]]\n| released   = 7 October 2016\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     = 2:52\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Armada Music|Armada]]|Mostiko}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Tony Hendrik|Dee Dee Halligan]]|Junior Torello|[[Lost Frequencies|Felix De Laet]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Hal Ritson]]|Felix De Laet}}\n| prev_title = [[Beautiful Life (Lost Frequencies song)|Beautiful Life]]\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = All or Nothing\n| next_year  = 2017\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|yXiP7h_BD1Q|\"What Is Love 2016\"}}}}\n}}\nIn 2016, Belgian DJ [[Lost Frequencies]] released a cover titled \"What Is Love 2016\", as a single from his debut album ''[[Less Is More (Lost Frequencies album)|Less Is More]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first= Hans |last= Op de Beeck |title= Wordt ook vierde single Lost Frequencies schot in de roos? \"Als het te slap is, dan is het gewoon te slap\" |newspaper= [[Het Laatste Nieuws]] |date= 7 October 2016 |accessdate= 8 October 2016 |url= http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/9092/Muzieknieuws/article/detail/2905385/2016/10/07/Wordt-ook-vierde-single-Lost-Frequencies-schot-in-de-roos-Als-het-te-slap-is-dan-is-het-gewoon-te-slap.dhtml |language= nl}}</ref> It was actually already produced back in 2014 as a remix for Jaymes Young's cover version of \"What is Love\". This version was remade for the album and became a hit on a number of European singles charts and topped the Belgian [[Ultratop]] Official Singles Chart.\n\n====Music video====\nAn official music video was released directed by Soulvizion. It features the Dutch professional [[basketball]] player [[Don Rigters]]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://social.quedeletras.com/lost-frequencies-what-is-love-2016/ |title= Lost Frequencies \u2013 What Is Love 2016 |work= Social M\u00fasica Musica |date= 7 October 2016 |accessdate= 16 November 2016}}</ref> who plays the role of David Rose, a basketball player who is severely injured trying to make a comeback to the game with encouragement from his girlfriend, (played by Melissa Kanza), his three teammates, (Alkenah Wansing, Jeroen Jansen and Lindy Chippendel) and by his basketball coach (played  by J E Rigters).\n\n====Track listing====\n*'''Armada / Mostiko, 7 October 2016'''\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" \u2013 2:52\n\n*'''Armada / Mostiko, 28 October 2016'''\n#What Is Love 2016\" ([[Regi Penxten|Regi]] & Lester Williams Remix) \u2013 4:21\n\n*'''Lost & Cie / Armada, 11 November 2016'''\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Regi & Lester Williams Remix) \u2013 3:08\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Regi & Lester Williams Extended Remix) \u2013 4:10\n\n*'''Armada / Mostiko, 6 January 2017'''\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" ([[Mike Mago]] Remix) \u2013 3:29\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" ([[Zonderling]] Remix) \u2013 3:11\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Galactic Marvl Remix) \u2013 2:54\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Rose Remix) \u2013 3:08\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Mike Mago Extended Remix) \u2013 5:49\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Zonderling Extended Remix) \u2013 4:27\n#\"What Is Love 2016\" (Rose Extended Remix) \u2013 4:08\n\n====Weekly charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2016\u20132017)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|20|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=1 December 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|1|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=23 November 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|12|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=3 December 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|92|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=23 November 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|24|songid=1597408|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=23 November 2016}}\n|-\n|Germany ([[German Airplay Chart|Airplay Chart]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Airplay Charts Deutschland \u2013 Woche 51/2016 |publisher= German Charts |accessdate= 30 January 2017 |url= http://germancharts.com/airplay_charts.asp?week=201651 |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n{{singlechart|Hungary|40|year=2016|week=48|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=10 December 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|73|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=10 December 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Poland|29|chartid=2217|year=2017|accessdate=6 February 2017|refname=Poland2}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakia|38|year=2016|week=50|accessdate=20 December 2016}}\n|-\n|Slovenia ([[SloTop50]])<ref>{{cite web|title= SloTop50 \u2013 Tedenska lestvica : 4 Teden 23.01.2017 \u2013 29.01.2017 |website= SloTop50 |accessdate= 29 August 2018 |url= https://www.slotop50.si/Glasbene-lestvice/Tedenske-lestvice/?year=2017&week=4}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|20 \n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|99|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=23 November 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|52|artist=Lost Frequencies|song=What Is Love 2016|accessdate=23 November 2016}}\n|}\n\n====Year-end charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2016)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|Belgium ([[Ultratop|Ultratop 50]] Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|title= Jaaroverzichten 2016 |publisher= [[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 29 December 2016 |url= http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=2016 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|41\n|}\n\n====Certifications====\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Belgium|type=single|artist=Lost Frequencies|title=What Is Love 2016|award=Platinum|number=2|relyear=2016|certyear=2019|accessdate=1 October 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|type=single|artist=Lost Frequencies|title=What Is Love 2016|award=Gold|relyear=2016|certyear=2017|accessdate=8 September 2017}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Dutch Top 40 number-one singles of 1993]]\n*[[List of number-one hits of 1993 (Austria)]]\n*[[List of number-one hits of 1993 (Italy)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1993 (Finland)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1993 (France)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1993 (Spain)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of the 1990s (Switzerland)#1993|List of number-one singles of the 1990s (Switzerland)]]\n*[[VG-lista 1964 to 1994]]\n*[[VRT Top 30 number-one hits of 1993]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Discogs release|149375|What Is Love|type=single}}\n*{{MetroLyrics song|haddaway|what-is-love}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Haddaway}}\n{{Lost Frequencies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:What Is Love (Song)}}\n[[Category:1993 debut singles]]\n[[Category:1993 songs]]\n[[Category:2009 singles]]\n[[Category:2016 singles]]\n[[Category:Dutch Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Single Top 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:European Hot 100 Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Haddaway songs]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Kiesza songs]]\n[[Category:Lost Frequencies songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Austria]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Finland]]\n[[Category:SNEP Top Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Italy]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Norway]]\n[[Ca